children.subject: I am not sure about the enrollment policy. But, 170 is a direct successor to 61B. It represents the mathematical side of what you learn in 61B, i.e. more focused on the different runtimes of the data structures you learn in 61B.
I was able to enroll in CS170 with just math 55, so if the enrollment is enforced then this is a new change.
Follow-up question: is math 55 and stat 134 a suitable replacement for CS70, or will the enrollment system prevent me from enrolling?

history.content:
Hello,

in the enrollment notes for 170, it says prerequisites will be enforced. I have taken cs70 ,but not 61b yet. However, in previous semesters,multiple people have been able to enroll in the class without the prerequisites. Is this a new enrollment change?

Would I still be able to enroll?

Also, would taking 61b concurrently work?

Thanks
